51:02.632 --> 51:06.136
Now back up.
Nice and easy.

51:06.171 --> 51:08.638
Turn around!
Hold it right there.

51:46.676 --> 51:48.178
The white fox?

51:48.213 --> 51:50.680
He left tracks across my behind.

51:50.715 --> 51:53.183
The black fox?

51:53.218 --> 51:55.185
Likewise.

52:20.710 --> 52:21.830
Body count is 6, lieutenant.

52:22.212 --> 52:23.213
Yeah.

52:23.248 --> 52:25.715
To steal junk, I can understand.

52:26.216 --> 52:28.718
A man is desperate,
he needs the money.

52:28.753 --> 52:30.720
But to kill for junk?
I don't get it.

52:31.221 --> 52:33.223
Don't be a boy scout, Goodman.

52:33.258 --> 52:35.725
A lot of people get killed
every day up here for nothing.

52:35.760 --> 52:39.229
What could be here that anyone
could possibly want that badly?

52:39.264 --> 52:41.731
$87,000.

52:41.766 --> 52:43.733
What?

52:43.768 --> 52:46.236
$87,000.

52:46.271 --> 52:47.737
Seen any cotton
around here lately?

52:47.772 --> 52:51.241
A bale of cotton, sure.

52:51.276 --> 52:53.243
Uncle Budd brought over
a bale of cotton.

52:53.278 --> 52:55.745
I bought it from him for $25.

52:57.247 --> 52:58.248
Where is it now?

52:58.283 --> 52:59.749
What?

52:59.784 --> 53:02.252
What happened to it?

53:02.287 --> 53:03.287
He came back later,

53:03.288 --> 53:06.756
he bought it back
from me for $30.

53:06.791 --> 53:08.758
He hauled it away.

53:08.793 --> 53:10.260
Wait a minute.

53:10.295 --> 53:13.263
He brought it in and then
he brung it out again?

53:13.763 --> 53:15.265
It don't add up, Goodman.

53:15.300 --> 53:16.300
That's what happened.

53:16.301 --> 53:18.768
Hauled it away where?

53:18.803 --> 53:21.271
He didn't say.

53:22.272 --> 53:25.275
Put out a reader on Uncle Budd.

53:25.310 --> 53:26.776
Come on, Digger.

53:29.779 --> 53:32.282
To kill for junk.

53:32.317 --> 53:36.286
Well! Did you find it?

53:36.321 --> 53:38.788
What do we got here,
an outraged citizen?

53:38.823 --> 53:40.290
Oh, Reverend O'Malley.

53:40.325 --> 53:42.292
Did you find the man who
stole my people's money?

53:42.792 --> 53:45.795
What were you doing at the junkyard
this hour of the night, Reverend?

53:46.296 --> 53:47.797
Holding a revival meeting?

53:50.300 --> 53:51.801
He was white, whoever he was.

53:51.836 --> 53:52.836
You know the man?

53:53.303 --> 53:54.583
What do you mean, do I know him?

53:54.804 --> 53:58.308
What I mean, sir, is did
you ever meet the man before?

53:58.343 --> 54:01.811
Oh, sure. Same one
who hijacked the rally.

54:01.846 --> 54:05.815
Funny. All the guys
at the rally had on masks.

54:05.850 --> 54:07.817
And, of course, you could
see right through the masks.

54:07.852 --> 54:11.821
Unless, of course, you knew
that they were white in advance.

54:12.322 --> 54:14.824
Have a cigarette.

54:15.825 --> 54:17.327
Where'd you get that?

54:17.362 --> 54:20.330
Mabel hill's apartment,
right where you left it.

54:29.839 --> 54:31.341
That's police brutality.

54:31.376 --> 54:32.376
No, Brother.

54:32.377 --> 54:34.344
That's cancer prevention.

54:34.379 --> 54:36.846
Reverend O'Malley, there are
6 dead bodies in the morgue.

54:36.881 --> 54:38.848
All we're asking you to do is
- now, look!

54:38.883 --> 54:40.350
How many times do I
have to tell you idiots?

54:40.385 --> 54:42.852
We're only asking you to tell
us what you know. Now, look!

54:42.887 --> 54:45.355
Easy, Digger, easy.

54:50.860 --> 54:54.864
Look, I am due in my pulpit
at 11:00 this morning,

54:54.899 --> 54:56.366
and if I ain't there-

54:56.401 --> 54:58.368
if my people were to find out

54:58.403 --> 55:00.370
that you had me locked up in this filthy,

55:00.405 --> 55:02.372
pissy pigsty, there'll be all hell to pay!

55:02.407 --> 55:05.375
What's that supposed to mean?

55:05.410 --> 55:06.876
Draw your own conclusions.

55:06.911 --> 55:09.379
And you can tell Bryce, the
commissioner, and the mayor!

55:09.414 --> 55:10.414
Reverend O'Malley-

55:10.880 --> 55:14.384
take me back
to my cell... honky!

55:16.886 --> 55:18.888
O'Malley!

55:18.923 --> 55:20.890
You forgot your lighter.

55:22.392 --> 55:24.894
Something else you forgot.

55:27.397 --> 55:29.399
Iris, baby, who hit you?

55:29.434 --> 55:30.900
You, you son of a bitch!

55:30.935 --> 55:32.902
But I got your black ass now! Cool it!

55:32.937 --> 55:35.405
Don't tell me to cool it!

55:35.440 --> 55:36.906
You left me for the cops.

55:36.941 --> 55:39.409
Nigger, I oughta kill you!

55:39.444 --> 55:40.910
You already did, baby.

55:40.945 --> 55:42.425
You have nailed his ass
onto the wall,

55:42.447 --> 55:43.913
right here in black and white.

55:43.948 --> 55:46.916
That's right.
I told them everything.

55:46.951 --> 55:48.418
I spilled my guts out.

55:48.918 --> 55:51.921
All about your phony
"back to Africa" swindle.

55:51.956 --> 55:52.956
Names, dates, places.

55:52.957 --> 55:55.425
The way you were gonna
hit all the big cities

55:55.460 --> 55:56.426
and get the money and split.

55:56.461 --> 55:58.928
Iris
- how you set up the switch at the rally,

55:58.963 --> 56:01.931
with the cat supposed to be
from the D.A.'s office.

56:01.966 --> 56:04.434
The way they were gonna pretend
to take you and the money downtown.

56:04.469 --> 56:06.936
But something happened,
and John hill got wasted.

56:07.437 --> 56:09.939
And Mabel hill found out and
was going straight to the cops.

56:09.974 --> 56:12.942
And you found her and tried
to kill her. That's a lie.

56:12.977 --> 56:15.945
I was there!
I saw you, you bastard!

56:15.980 --> 56:18.448
You took that ship, that big,
old black ship black beauty,

56:18.483 --> 56:21.451
and you smashed it down
on that poor girl's head.

56:21.486 --> 56:23.953
I never touched that boat!

56:23.988 --> 56:24.988
Fractured skull.

56:24.989 --> 56:25.989
Negative.

56:25.990 --> 56:27.957
Assault with intent to kill.

56:27.992 --> 56:30.460
If she dies, it's murder one.

56:30.495 --> 56:32.462
Which means we burn you.

56:34.464 --> 56:35.965
Burn me?

56:36.466 --> 56:37.467
Burn me with what?

56:39.469 --> 56:41.471
Lieutenant!

56:41.506 --> 56:42.972
I hope that some
of you damn fools

56:43.007 --> 56:45.487
had the good sense to examine
that model boat for fingerprints.

56:45.510 --> 56:46.976
Of course we did, Reverend.

56:47.011 --> 56:49.479
Tell these two dumb-ass
uncle tom nigger cops of yours

56:49.979 --> 56:52.482
whose prints you found on that boat
- that broad's or mine?

56:52.517 --> 56:55.985
He did it! He took those
people's money. He did it!

56:56.486 --> 56:58.988
You shut your mouth!
I'll get you, O'Malley!

56:59.023 --> 57:01.991
I swear on my mother's grave
I'll get you for this!

57:02.026 --> 57:03.993
I swear I will!
I'll get you!

57:17.323 --> 57:18.825
One more word, soul Brother.

57:19.826 --> 57:20.827
You had it made.

57:21.327 --> 57:23.830
Black folks would have
followed you anywhere.

57:24.330 --> 57:25.832
You could have been
another Marcus Garvey

57:25.867 --> 57:26.907
or even another Malcolm x.

57:27.333 --> 57:29.836
But instead, you ain't nothin'

57:29.871 --> 57:32.338
but a pimp with
a chickenshit backbone.

57:39.846 --> 57:42.849
Break his Goddamn head.

57:42.884 --> 57:43.884
No.

57:43.885 --> 57:47.353
Keep him on ice for 24 hours.

57:47.388 --> 57:49.355
Then he'll bust his own head.

57:49.856 --> 57:50.857
24 hours?

57:50.892 --> 57:53.359
Bryce'll never stand for it.

57:53.394 --> 57:54.394
The hell with Bryce!

57:54.395 --> 57:56.863
O'Malley'll break.

57:56.898 --> 57:58.364
Not only for us.

57:58.399 --> 58:00.366
Everybody in Harlem
will know the son of a bitch

58:00.401 --> 58:01.868
for the evil bastard that he is.

58:02.368 --> 58:04.871
You hold him one more day.

58:04.906 --> 58:06.506
Don't you guys ever
listen to the buzzer?

58:06.873 --> 58:07.873
What's up?

58:07.874 --> 58:08.875
The word just came
over the squawk box.

58:08.910 --> 58:10.376
They just found Uncle Budd.

58:10.411 --> 58:11.878
Did they find a bale of cotton?

58:11.913 --> 58:14.881
Don't ask me.
Ask the squawk box.

58:19.886 --> 58:21.387
Poor Uncle Budd.

58:21.422 --> 58:22.422
What do you suppose

58:22.889 --> 58:24.390
they did to him?

58:24.425 --> 58:27.393
My guess'd be the river.

58:27.428 --> 58:29.896
Oh, my God.

58:31.397 --> 58:32.899
We're dragging the river, Luddy.

58:32.934 --> 58:33.934
You set it up.

58:33.935 --> 58:35.401
Yes, sir.

58:40.406 --> 58:43.409
White fox tasted black blood.

58:43.444 --> 58:44.911
Maybe yes,

58:44.946 --> 58:46.412
and maybe no.

58:46.913 --> 58:48.414
Where the hell's that rabbit?

58:48.449 --> 58:49.916
All right, stop it.

58:49.951 --> 58:51.417
A vicious son of a bitch
murders Uncle Budd,

58:51.452 --> 58:53.419
and you two talk nonsense.

58:54.921 --> 58:57.924
You gotta look on the bright
side, lieutenant.

58:58.424 --> 58:59.425
You saw that white
joker last night.

58:59.460 --> 59:00.460
You identify him?

59:01.928 --> 59:03.429
I don't know, lieutenant.

59:03.464 --> 59:04.931
Maybe yes, maybe no.

59:05.431 --> 59:07.934
All those kind of people
look alike to me.

59:08.434 --> 59:10.436
Cut the crap.
That's an order.

59:10.937 --> 59:12.537
Drop whatever the hell
else you're doing,

59:12.939 --> 59:14.440
and you find him!
And that's final.

59:14.475 --> 59:17.443
We're going home

59:17.478 --> 59:20.446
we're going to see the sun

59:20.481 --> 59:22.949
going home

59:22.984 --> 59:26.452
a new life has begun

59:26.487 --> 59:27.954
we're going home

59:27.989 --> 59:29.455
oh, yes?

59:29.490 --> 59:31.958
Where we can all be free

59:32.458 --> 59:34.460
in the land where there's sand

59:34.961 --> 59:37.463
and I got liberty

59:37.498 --> 59:38.498
so steal away

59:38.965 --> 59:42.468
my Lord, steal away

59:44.005 --> 59:45.471
take me

59:45.506 --> 59:47.473
and I will tell you

59:47.508 --> 59:49.475
we're going home

59:49.976 --> 59:51.477
oh, going home!

59:51.978 --> 59:56.482
Hey, children, going home

59:56.517 --> 59:57.517
wait here.

59:57.518 --> 01:00:00.987
We're going home

01:00:01.022 --> 01:00:03.489
where this world was born

01:00:03.990 --> 01:00:08.494
and where life with the strife
won't be tight

01:00:08.529 --> 01:00:09.996
we're going home

01:00:10.031 --> 01:00:11.998
captain, O'Malley's
people are coming.

01:00:12.033 --> 01:00:14.500
O'Malley's people?

01:00:16.502 --> 01:00:19.505
Just like the good book said

01:00:19.540 --> 01:00:22.008
we're going home

01:00:22.043 --> 01:00:23.043
Brothers and Sisters,

01:00:23.044 --> 01:00:24.010
we have marched all the way

01:00:24.045 --> 01:00:26.512
from O'Malley's tabernacle
this afternoon,

01:00:26.547 --> 01:00:29.015
not merely for the purpose
of gift-bringing,

01:00:29.050 --> 01:00:32.018
but to offer prayers
for his release.

01:00:32.053 --> 01:00:33.053
Amen.
Amen.

01:00:33.054 --> 01:00:35.021
What do you think?

01:00:35.521 --> 01:00:36.522
How many men we got?

01:00:37.023 --> 01:00:39.525
It's Sunday.
Half the men are off.

01:00:39.560 --> 01:00:42.028
All right. You better
send out a recall.

01:00:42.063 --> 01:00:43.529
Station house alert.

01:00:43.564 --> 01:00:44.530
We'll try to hold this
right where it is,

01:00:45.031 --> 01:00:48.034
but if anything happens,
if it gets out of control,

01:00:48.069 --> 01:00:50.036
go to signal 1039.

01:00:50.071 --> 01:00:51.537
Ok.

01:00:51.572 --> 01:00:59.572
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:01:06.552 --> 01:01:14.552
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:01:23.104 --> 01:01:24.570
People, just settle down.

01:01:27.573 --> 01:01:30.076
Hey, what the hell
is going on here?

01:01:30.576 --> 01:01:31.576
Riot.

01:01:31.577 --> 01:01:39.577
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:01:41.587 --> 01:01:44.590
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:01:44.625 --> 01:01:47.093
I figure about a 4-block
area, commissioner.

01:01:47.128 --> 01:01:48.594
What are you
standing there for?!

01:01:49.095 --> 01:01:50.096
Get out and get those riot guns!

01:01:50.131 --> 01:01:52.598
I don't give a damn!
Find ed and Digger

01:01:52.633 --> 01:01:54.100
if it takes all afternoon!

01:01:54.600 --> 01:01:55.760
Hold 'em right
where they are-

01:02:02.058 --> 01:02:03.298
now that I have your attention,

01:02:03.559 --> 01:02:04.560
let's bow our heads.

01:02:05.061 --> 01:02:06.562
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:02:07.063 --> 01:02:10.066
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:02:10.566 --> 01:02:14.070
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:02:14.570 --> 01:02:16.572
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:02:17.073 --> 01:02:19.075
Who the hell
asked you to come here?

01:02:23.079 --> 01:02:24.580
He will be free,

01:02:24.615 --> 01:02:26.082
but not this way.

01:02:29.085 --> 01:02:31.587
Jarema, they're gonna
try to take O'Malley.

01:02:33.589 --> 01:02:35.591
Don't you worry, Reverend.

01:02:36.092 --> 01:02:38.094
I know how to use this thing,
and I'll protect you

01:02:38.129 --> 01:02:39.595
with the last breath in my body.

01:02:39.630 --> 01:02:43.599
Oh, I know you will, officer.

01:02:43.634 --> 01:02:45.601
I know you will.

01:02:52.108 --> 01:02:53.609
Get out of here!

01:03:02.118 --> 01:03:03.619
Hold it there.

01:03:04.120 --> 01:03:06.122
Now cool it!

01:03:19.635 --> 01:03:21.137
Hold it!

01:03:22.138 --> 01:03:23.639
Quiet down!

01:03:25.141 --> 01:03:27.143
All right, get inside.

01:03:27.643 --> 01:03:29.145
What in the Goddamn hell?

01:03:29.645 --> 01:03:30.646
Let 'em inside, officers.

01:03:32.148 --> 01:03:33.149
All right, take those
guns out of here.

01:03:33.184 --> 01:03:34.184
We'll take it from here.

01:03:37.153 --> 01:03:38.154
Hold it!

01:03:38.189 --> 01:03:41.157
Hold it right there!

01:03:41.192 --> 01:03:42.658
Hey, we know what you cops do

01:03:42.693 --> 01:03:43.693
in the precinct basement.

01:03:44.160 --> 01:03:46.162
How do we know
Deke O'Malley ain't dead?

01:03:46.197 --> 01:03:49.165
'Cause I say he ain't!
And I'm the doctor.

01:03:49.200 --> 01:03:51.667
You filthy pigs!

01:03:53.169 --> 01:03:54.670
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:03:54.705 --> 01:03:56.672
Shut up, white boy!

01:03:56.707 --> 01:03:58.674
I'm talking about my money!

01:03:58.709 --> 01:04:00.676
Me and my family

01:04:00.711 --> 01:04:04.180
put up $1,000, and we ain't
heard from it since.

01:04:05.181 --> 01:04:08.184
If you police don't
do something, we will.

01:04:08.219 --> 01:04:09.685
Tear the damn precinct down!

01:04:09.720 --> 01:04:12.188
Burn the mother to the ground!

01:04:13.689 --> 01:04:14.690
Give us our money!

01:04:14.725 --> 01:04:16.192
I want my money now!

01:04:16.692 --> 01:04:17.693
I want my money, man.

01:04:26.202 --> 01:04:27.203
Shut up!

01:04:29.705 --> 01:04:31.707
Digger and I
will do our damnedest

01:04:31.742 --> 01:04:34.210
to get the money back.
We promise.

01:04:34.245 --> 01:04:35.711
Hell with promises!

01:04:35.746 --> 01:04:36.746
Anybody out there

01:04:36.747 --> 01:04:38.214
ever heard coffin ed
or the grave Digger

01:04:38.249 --> 01:04:39.715
make a promise we didn't keep?

01:04:43.219 --> 01:04:45.221
We may have broken some heads,

01:04:45.256 --> 01:04:48.224
but we never broke no promises.

01:04:51.727 --> 01:04:53.229
Now go on home!

01:04:54.730 --> 01:04:56.732
Fascist pigs!

01:04:56.767 --> 01:04:59.235
Free Deke O'Malley!

01:05:06.242 --> 01:05:07.743
Commie pigs!

01:05:07.778 --> 01:05:09.745
Fascist commies!

01:05:43.279 --> 01:05:44.780
Where the hell you going?

01:05:44.815 --> 01:05:47.283
Well, ain't this
the going-back-to-Africa rally?

01:05:47.318 --> 01:05:48.784
No, Brother. It is
the going-home rally.

01:05:48.819 --> 01:05:50.286
Now move it.

01:06:20.816 --> 01:06:22.318
Sergeant, my name is Callahan.

01:06:22.818 --> 01:06:23.819
I'm the attorney
for Reverend O'Malley.

01:06:24.320 --> 01:06:25.520
I have a writ for his release,

01:06:25.821 --> 01:06:26.822
signed by Judge Glossner.

01:06:27.323 --> 01:06:27.823
This'll take a few minutes.

01:06:28.324 --> 01:06:30.326
Ok. I'll go down
and tell him.

01:06:30.361 --> 01:06:32.328
I thank all of you.

01:06:32.363 --> 01:06:35.831
I'm obliged to you
for coming down here

01:06:35.866 --> 01:06:38.334
and bringing this great food
for me and my fellow prisoners.

01:06:38.369 --> 01:06:39.835
Amen.
Amen.

01:06:39.870 --> 01:06:42.838
Inasmuch as you've done unto
one of these, my little ones,

01:06:42.873 --> 01:06:43.873
you've done unto me.

01:06:43.874 --> 01:06:44.874
Amen.
Amen.

01:06:44.875 --> 01:06:46.342
Just the way you wanted it.

01:06:46.842 --> 01:06:48.344
Praise the Lord, Brother, amen.

01:06:48.379 --> 01:06:49.379
What about your tray,

01:06:49.380 --> 01:06:50.846
Sister Minnie?

01:06:50.881 --> 01:06:52.348
It's all yours, Reverend.

01:06:52.383 --> 01:06:54.850
I thank you, Sister,
but I'd be much obliged

01:06:55.351 --> 01:06:58.354
if you'd take that tray over
to Sister Iris over there.

01:06:59.855 --> 01:07:01.357
Well, if you say so, Reverend.

01:07:01.392 --> 01:07:03.359
I do say so, Sister.

01:07:06.362 --> 01:07:07.863
And, Sister Minnie,

01:07:07.898 --> 01:07:10.866
the Lord loveth
a cheerful giver.

01:07:10.901 --> 01:07:11.901
Amen.
Amen.

01:07:11.902 --> 01:07:12.902
Amen.

01:07:17.990 --> 01:07:20.376
A jealous hysterical woman...

01:07:21.877 --> 01:07:25.881
will do anything, including
lie, to hurt O'Malley.

01:07:26.382 --> 01:07:27.383
Is that the case?

01:07:27.418 --> 01:07:29.885
No. There's a bale
of cotton,

01:07:29.920 --> 01:07:31.387
the white man
that Digger spotted,

01:07:31.887 --> 01:07:33.889
the shoot-out,
and the vicious murder

01:07:33.924 --> 01:07:34.890
of Booker Washington Simms.

01:07:34.925 --> 01:07:35.925
Who?

01:07:35.926 --> 01:07:37.893
Uncle Budd, the old junk dealer.

01:07:37.928 --> 01:07:39.895
We're still dragging
the river for his body.

01:07:39.930 --> 01:07:41.397
And all Ed and Digger want to do

01:07:41.897 --> 01:07:42.898
is hold O'Malley

01:07:42.933 --> 01:07:44.400
for one more day.

01:07:44.435 --> 01:07:45.435
What?

01:07:45.436 --> 01:07:47.403
They think
that they can-

01:07:47.903 --> 01:07:50.023
don't tell me what they think.
Tell me what you think.

01:07:50.906 --> 01:07:53.409
Or don't you do that anymore?

